<TITLE> CA condemns assassination attempt on Karzai </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 27 (bdnews24.com)Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed Sunday condemned an assassination attempt on Afghan president Hamid Karzai. "The chief adviser expressed his grave concern over the cowardly attack on the life of president Hamid Karzai in Kabul," the government said in a statement issued by the foreign ministry. Fakhruddin expressed his happiness that the Afghan president had escaped the assassination bid. Karzai was hustled away but escaped unhurt after the assassination attempt during an official celebration in the Afghan capital on Sunday. bdn
